If we decide to move forward with your application, the Amazon recruiting team will reach out to discuss next steps. Any updates to your application status will be reflected on your Application dashboard, so be sure to check back regularly. Go to your application dashboard Explore our interview resources for more information on the hiring process and how to prepare for interviews. To learn more about our peculiar culture, visit Amazon.jobs , and get the latest Amazon news and stories by following our Day One blog . email subject: Thank you for applying for the Engineering Intern, Core PPM Platform (Summer 2025) Role at Illumio!
email body: Thank you for applying! Hi Srisankaet, Thank you for submitting your application to the Engineering Intern, Core PPM Platform (Summer 2025) role and your interest to join us at Illumio – where we're not just about technology; we're about a brighter, safer digital future. Your interest in being part of our mission to redefine breach containment and bring unparalleled security to communications between workloads and devices has us genuinely excited! What to Expect Working with Us: At Illumio, we're committed to innovation that lights up the digital landscape, making it a safer place for everyone. Our platform for breach containment represents a groundbreaking step in securing digital communications and assets. By joining our team, you'll play a critical role in crafting solutions that not only protect but also illuminate the future of digital security. A Few Reminders: Stay Engaged: We encourage you to learn more about our groundbreaking work by visiting our website and following us on our social media channels. Ask Questions: If you have any questions about the role, our process, or anything else, please don't hesitate to reach out. We value open communication and are here to provide clarity and support. Reflect on Our Core Values: As you prepare for potential next steps, consider how our core values resonate with your personal and professional journey. We're looking for individuals who are not only skilled but also passionate about moving onwards, together, towards a brighter future. We truly appreciate your interest in Illumio and your desire to contribute to a world where digital safety is not just a goal, but a reality. We're thrilled to potentially have you join us on this journey. Warmest regards, The Illumio Talent Acquisition Team

email subject: Peachtree Application Price
email body: Hello, My prospective roommates (cc’d) and I are trying to filling out the application for The Mark for the Fall ’25-Spring ’26 cycle. We are looking into the 4x4 Peachtree units. We started the application several weeks ago but could not complete it because of the restrictions of your guarantor program. Being international students, it was hard for us to find a guarantor and complete that section of the application. Now that we have all the details, we are ready to fill out the application. However, we now see no longer see the $1355 price tag on the application portal. Instead it lists $1425. We have been on several calls with the leasing office and they let us know that the official price is still $1355 (as listed on your website as well). We’d appreciate if you could help us completing the application and keeping the $1355 price for the Peachtree. We’re still really interested in the Mark apartments and would love to complete the application at the earliest. Thanks, Rahul +1 (470)461-4339

email subject: Re: Peachtree Application Price

email subject: Priority Application Deadline Coming Up - Dec. 2
email body: Choose your deadline + Join us online for live Q&A! Dear Srisankaet, A future at Carnegie Mellon University is in your hands! The PRIORITY deadline is coming up on December 2, 2024. Submit your online application form and required supporting materials by the priority deadline to receive a decision by the end of January . The required supporting materials are two (2) recommendations, official transcript/evaluation report for your bachelor's degree, and official test scores (if applicable) . Review the application checklist for more details. Applicants who are currently pursuing their bachelor’s degree are encouraged to apply by the REGULAR deadline (January 10, 2025) in order to allow for your fall (or seventh) semester grades to be included on your official transcript/evaluation report. Regardless of which deadline you are applying for, we would like to remind you that CMU's Heinz College does not charge an application fee (it's free to apply!!) . We invite you to join our upcoming "Ask us Anything" live chat sessions on November 18th (12:00pm ET) and December 2nd (9:00am ET). Register to attend an 'Ask us Anything' live chat session! >> Good news!… If you are not seeking out a decision by late January, we do allow a grace period for your supporting materials to reach us. Your official test scores (if applicable), transcript/evaluation report and recommendation forms (uploaded online) may all arrive AFTER the deadline without impacting your application or opportunity for scholarship. Many FAQs can be answered by visiting our website, heinz.cmu.edu ! If you’d prefer to view previously recorded webinars or our Fall Open House sessions , you will find lots of specific program content. As always, feel free to contact us at 412-268-2164 or hnzadmit@andrew.cmu.edu . Warm regards, David ________________ David Eber Executive Director of Admissions and Financial Aid Heinz College of Information Systems and Public Policy Carnegie Mellon University Office of Admissions and Financial Aid Heinz College of Information Systems & Public Policy Carnegie Mellon University 5000 Forbes Ave. 1101 Hamburg Hall Pittsburgh, PA 15213-3890 hnzadmit@andrew.cmu.edu | +1.412.268.2164 Copyright © 2024-2025 Carnegie Mellon University's Heinz College, All rights reserved. This email was sent to srisankaetgt@gmail.com by CMU's Heinz College Admissions. Unsubscribe from Carnegie Mellon University's Heinz College Office of Admissions.

email subject: You’re invited: Hear from our recruiter panel on how to make your application and interview shine!
email body: Hey there, Are you nervous about landing the right job or internship this fall? Tune in to our upcoming recruiter panel to hear advice from the ones reviewing applications and conducting interviews! We're excited to host McMaster-Carr, Oliver Wyman, and a few additional companies (TBA) to share their top tips to make your application stand out from a sea of applicants. Learn more and RSVP below! What You'll Learn How to tailor your resume for a role Tips for networking on LinkedIn How to determine if you have the right experience level for a role What kinds of questions you'll be asked in first round interviews and how to impress recruiters How to be successful in follow-up interviews, including how to ace behavioral interviews From specific resume tweaks to the right way to network on LinkedIn to common interview structures, you’ll hear actionable advice for making the most of your job search this fall. Our recruiter guests will also be reviewing submitted questions through the Q&A functionality, so it’s a great opportunity to have your biggest questions answered. RSVP here to tune in or to receive the recording. Best, Kate Beckman Director, Brand & Community Click here to unsubscribe

email subject: Submitting Your Application After The Deadline
email body: Dear Srisankaet, Thank you for your interest in Carnegie Mellon University’s Heinz College of Information Systems & Public Policy. Although the priority deadline has passed, it is our policy to continue accepting applications until space is no longer available in the incoming class for our master's programs. That point in time varies from year to year. Therefore, if you are still considering applying for admission to the Fall 2024 incoming class, we encourage you to submit your application no later than February 1, 2024 . In order to SUBMIT your application by February 1, 2024 you’ll need to complete the following: Answer the required questions within the online application form Upload essay Upload CV/ résumé Register your recommenders' names and email addresses Enter test date and registration number for any required standardized test(s) if applicable (GRE/GMAT is optional for 2024) As a reminder, we don't charge a fee for you to apply. That's right! We do NOT charge an application fee! We do allow a grace period for supporting materials (transcript(s), recommendations and/or test scores) to reach us. All supporting materials may arrive AFTER February 1st (their arrival after the 1st will NOT have a negative impact on your admission decision or scholarship review!). If you have specific questions or concerns that are preventing you from completing your application before the end of this month, please don't hesitate to call us at 412-268-2164 or email us at hnzadmit@andrew.cmu.edu . As a top-ranked institution, Heinz College strives to make a graduate education accessible to talented students through numerous fellowship and scholarship opportunities. Applications submitted by February 1st will be given full consideration for this funding. COMPLETE YOUR APPLICATION NOW! > We look forward to receiving your application to our master's program soon. Sincerely, David ________________ David Eber Executive Director of Admissions and Financial Aid Heinz College of Information Systems and Public Policy Carnegie Mellon University 412-268-2164 Learn about our Application for Admission . Meet us on campus , on the road , or on a webinar ! Sent by Office of Admissions and Financial Aid Heinz College of Information Systems & Public Policy Carnegie Mellon University 5000 Forbes Ave. 1101 Hamburg Hall Pittsburgh, PA 15213-3890 hnzadmit@andrew.cmu.edu | +1.412.268.2164 Copyright © 2023-2024 Carnegie Mellon University's Heinz College, All rights reserved. email subject: Update on your Skydio Application
email body: Hi Srisankaet, Thank you for applying for the Mobile Software Engineering Intern role at Skydio ! We know that there are lots of exciting companies out there, so we appreciate the time you took to apply to ours. After reviewing your application, we have unfortunately decided not to move forward at this time. While we greatly appreciate your interest in Skydio, we ultimately decided to proceed with other candidates whose skills and experience align more closely with our needs for this specific role. If you submitted an application to other roles at Skydio and haven't heard back, then your resume is still under review and we will be in touch soon with an update. Our hiring priorities are constantly evolving, so we encourage you to keep an eye on our jobs page. If you see another role that seems like a good fit, please don't hesitate to apply. In the meantime, we'd like to thank you again for your interest and we wish you all the best in your job search. Cheers, Skydio Talent Team

email subject: Application Deadline Coming Up
email body: Happy New Year from Heinz College! Dear Srisankaet, Happy New Year from all of us at Carnegie Mellon University’s Heinz College of Information Systems and Public Policy! We noticed that you have not yet started your application for admission to the graduate programs at Carnegie Mellon University’s Heinz College. We would like to let you know that you still have time and it is free to apply (no application fee!) . The application deadline is Wednesday, January 10, 2024 . Please know that our staff would be more than happy to answer any questions (via email or phone) that you might have regarding our application process. We also welcome you to join our upcoming "Ask us Anything" live chat sessions TOMORROW, January 4th at 9:00am and 12:00pm EST. REGISTER TO ATTEND A LIVE CHAT SESSION >> Good news!… We do allow a grace period for your supporting materials to reach us. Your official test scores (if applicable), transcript/evaluation report and recommendation forms (uploaded online) may all arrive AFTER the deadline without impacting your application or opportunity for scholarship. Many FAQs can be answered by visiting our website, heinz.cmu.edu ! email subject: Application Deadline: January 10, 2024
email body: Join our upcoming Chat Sessions Dear Srisankaet, Have questions about scholarships, the admissions process, or something else Heinz College-related? You can ask us anything! Join us for our upcoming live chat sessions ahead of the January 10th application deadline —our admissions team is here to answer any last-minute questions you have before you hit submit ! LIVE CHAT SESSIONS! - REGISTER TO ATTEND >> December 12, 2023 | 9:00AM - 10:00AM (EST) December 12, 2023 | 12:00PAM - 1:00PM (EST) January 4, 2024 | 9:00AM - 10:00AM (EST) January 4, 2024 | 12:00PM - 1:00PM (EST) Many FAQs can be answered by visiting our website, heinz.cmu.edu ! If you’d prefer to view previously recorded webinars or our Fall Open House sessions , you will find lots of specific program content. Remember, in order to SUBMIT your application by the posted deadline, you'll need to complete the following: Answer required questions within the online application form Upload essay Upload CV/ résumé Register your recommenders' names and email addresses Enter test date and registration number for any required standardized test(s) We don’t expect to receive your transcript(s), recommendations or your test scores (if applicable) by the deadline. The arrival of these materials after the deadline will NOT have a negative impact on your admission decision or scholarship review! As always, feel free to contact us at 412-268-2164 or hnzadmit@andrew.cmu.edu . email subject: 📅 [Invitation] Google Cloud Applied AI Summit
email body: 📅 [Invitation] Google Cloud Applied AI Summit Hi Sankaet, Join us at Google Cloud's Applied AI Summit on December 13, 2023! The summit is a no-cost, digital event with practical sessions and demos for developers of all skill levels. This year's focus: generative AI. Register Here Be sure to check out the talk by Kaggle's Developer Relations Lead, Phil Culliton, titled "Prototyping useful applications on Kaggle" . He'll walk you through how to experiment with your LLM application ideas on Kaggle’s no-cost hardware alongside our community of learners and experts. You'll learn how to build a simple retrieval augmented generation (RAG) application, explore your options for moving beyond a proof of concept, and examine Kaggle’s hardware options. See you there, The Kaggle Team Kaggle, Inc 1600 Amphitheatre Pkwy Mountain View, CA 94043 This email was sent to srisankaetgt@gmail.com because you indicated that you'd like to receive news and updates about Kaggle. If you don't want to receive these emails in the future, please unsubscribe here . You can also change your preferences on your account's profile page by logging in at kaggle.com.

email subject: Complete Your Netflix Software Engineering Internship Application | Next Steps
email body: Hi Srisankaet, Thank you for your interest in our Netflix Software Engineering Internship role! In order for your application to be reviewed, please complete this Airtable form . Your application will only be considered complete after you submit this form in conjunction with the application you already submitted on our Netflix Careers site. Please only complete the form once; duplicate submissions will not be considered. Due to the large volume of applications we receive, we're sorry that we're unable to personally follow up with each applicant. Our full recruiting process may take several weeks, so we kindly ask for your patience as we complete candidate reviews and interviews. In order to maintain a fair and equitable hiring process, we will not be able to accommodate very tight deadlines. For applicants selected to proceed, the interview process will begin with a CodeSignal Assessment. The results from this assessment will be used as just one additional data point to determine who will be invited to the interview rounds. The first two rounds of interviews are technical/coding interviews with Netflix software engineers, and the final round with consist of both technical and behavioral questions. Your advancement will be based on the feedback at each round. Important Note : If you're selected to move forward, the next email you receive will come from CodeSignal; we strongly recommend adding no-reply@codesignal.com to your contacts to prevent spam filtering. Our goal is to reach out to candidates who are chosen for initial next steps within the next two to three weeks. If you haven’t heard from us by then, we may have reached interview capacity. Note that our Software Engineering intern interview process is designed to assess your generalist skills, coding fundamentals, and aptitude. Offers will be extended to join our 2024 Intern class at Netflix, where we’ll have 3 start date options in Summer 2024 to centralize onboarding programming and training. Thanks again, and good luck! -The Netflix Emerging Talent Team

email subject: Thanks for applying for the Software Engineer Intern - Backend/Full-stack (Boulder, CO - Summer 2024) (28269) position at Splunk!
email body: Hi Srisankaet, Thank you for your interest in the Software Engineer Intern - Backend/Full-stack (Boulder, CO - Summer 2024) (ID: 28269) position at Splunk! We're always looking for top talent and we are thrilled to receive your application. You can view the status of your application here: Application Status . Need an accommodation or reasonable adjustment made during the application and recruiting process? Submit a request via interview accommodation/adjustment request form . What happens next? We’ll review the resumes and make some decisions. If we’re interested in moving forward, one of our recruiters will contact you personally. If your application is unsuccessful or you withdraw from the process or decline an offer, your application data will be kept on file as long as required by law. Unless you have told us not to, we may also use your data to inform you about other interesting jobs that match your skill set. You can tell us at any time that you no longer want this by submitting your request through our data request portal. Either way, we strongly recommend signing up for our job alerts so you can keep up to date on the latest openings. What can you do while we review your application? While we spend some time getting to know more about you, we encourage you to do the same with us. - A good starting point is our Careers Page where you can learn what makes Splunk such a great place to work. - Visit our Benefits Page to see the next-level benefits our Splunkers enjoy. - Check out the Splunk Life Blog to get a sense of what our amazing people are like. - On the Splunk4Good Page Page, you can see how we’re using our technology, expertise, and talent to address important social issues. - Connect with us on Linkedin , Facebook , Instagram , and Twitter . - It feels nice to get awards but we’re especially proud (and humbled) when we’re named to those “Best Workplace for_____” lists. You can find all of them on our Awards Page . Also, if you have a couple of minutes, would you mind taking a quick five-question survey about the application process? Your responses are confidential. Splunk will not know the identity of the respondents. Data will be used in aggregate to inform improvements to our processes. Take the survey Again, thank you for applying! Sincerely, The Splunk Talent Acquisition Team Splunk’s Career Site Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, store and share your information when you apply for a position at Splunk. This message is intended only for the personal, confidential, and authorized use of the recipient(s) named above. If you are not that person, you are not authorized to review, use, copy, forward, distribute or otherwise disclose the information contained in the message. -*_____ You can reply directly to this message or click here to reply via your Jobvite user account. email subject: Thank You for Applying to FiscalNote!
email body: Hello Srisankaet, Thank you for your interest in the FiscalNote AI Internship position with FiscalNote, the award-winning global leader of SaaS technology-powered market intelligence and public policy! We are very excited to receive your application, and our team will carefully review your skills and qualifications to determine if there is alignment with the current opening. We understand how challenging the job search process can be and appreciate that you chose to apply to FiscalNote. Because of that, we pledge to treat your application with the dignity, respect, and consideration it deserves while striving to ensure every candidate receives a response to their application. As a result, you should expect to hear from us within the next few weeks. In the meantime, we encourage you to learn more about what makes FiscalNote an incredible place to work! Our seven core values serve as our ‘North Star’ - not only in the way we do business but also in how we collaborate and innovate across the organization to achieve our goals in a people-first mindset. FiscalNote offers a comprehensive total rewards package and has received multiple awards recognizing our devotion to our employees and our unique and special culture, which you can check out here . If you truly want to make a difference in the world, you’ve come to the right place! Our mission, vision, and purpose are unlike any other. Want to know more? Hear directly from our CEO Tim Hwang about his inspiring vision for FiscalNote, and stay up-to-date with the many exciting announcements our company has recently made. Of course, if you have any questions, please don’t hesitate to reach out to recruiting.team@fiscalnote.com . Again, we want to thank you for considering FiscalNote as part of your future career, we warmly appreciate your time and interest, and we look forward to being in touch soon. Thank you, FiscalNote Recruiting Follow us on LinkedIn!

email body: Dear Srisankaet Cheemalamarri, We are excited to see that you have applied for a position at IBM, and we want to ensure that you have the best opportunity to showcase your fantastic skills. We understand that resume alone doesn't always reflect a candidate's full potential. That's why we invite you to complete one or more of the following assessments, which will help us gain a more comprehensive view of your capabilities. IBM values accessibility and are committed to ensuring that every candidate has an equal opportunity to showcase their skills and potential. We support measures like additional time for persons with disabilities on selection assessments. We use following assessments for selection purposes. You will be invited to complete 1 or more of these assessments, depending on the role you are applying for. The next step in the process includes one or more assessments – described below. The Coding Assessment - helps us to understand your level of programming knowledge and ability. You will be presented with a coding interface to solve coding challenges. This is a timed assessment. The Video Assessment - helps us to get to know more about you and your skills. You will be presented with a pre-recorded question, and you will be asked to record your response using a webcam and microphone. This is a timed assessment. We believe that these assessments will provide you with a better opportunity to showcase your skills, and we encourage you to take them seriously. We also want to make sure that you feel comfortable and supported throughout the process. All applicants are requested to click the accommodation link below. If you are a person with a disability, please follow the link to submit any adjustments that you require, such as extra time. IBM will review the details of your requirement and work with you on any adjustment options for your application. It is important that you submit your requirements before starting any assessments. If you do not need extra time on the assessments, please mark your response in the link below. Accommodation Form Please note that this form must be completed for each position you apply for that requires an assessment. For additional information and helpful tips, please visit our blog We appreciate your interest in joining our team and wish you the best of luck as you complete these assessments. We can't wait to see all that you have to offer! Sincerely, The IBM Talent Acquisition Team 655498BR Data Scientist Intern 2024

email subject: Regarding your application to Modernizing Medicine, Inc.
email body: Hello, We are thrilled to hear of your interest in ModMed's software development internship program for summer 2024! We are attending the Georgia Tech College of Computing Career Fair on September 14th, 2023, at the Mercedes-Benz Stadium from 9:30 a.m. to 3:30 p.m. It's going to be an amazing event, and we would be delighted to meet you in person and discuss any available opportunities. To ensure you get a chance to meet us, let us know if you would like to be added to our list of candidates visiting us at the fair. You will have the opportunity to meet Dan Pierce, our VP of Engineering, and Fayaz Adam, our Software Engineering Supervisor, both of whom are fellow Georgia Tech alumni. If you're unable to attend, we'd still love to consider you for our 2024 Internship Program. Following the fair, we will be reviewing resumes and actively recruiting for our product development internship and co-op programs over the coming weeks. If you have any questions, please do not hesitate to contact us. We cannot wait to hear from you and potentially welcome you to our team! Warm Regards, Shiraz Menchari

email subject: Thank you for applying to HubSpot
email body: Hi Srisankaet! We’ve received your application for the HubSpot Software Engineer Internship & Co-op Program (USA) position at HubSpot. Thank you for your interest in joining the HubSpot team! We’ll review your information and if your background looks like a match, we’ll reach out to schedule the next steps. We’re excited to share that HubSpot is growing and with that, we see a large amount of applications for each role. While we do this, we will not share your application information with anyone outside the HubSpot team except where necessary to assist us in assessing your candidacy throughout the recruitment process. That means your data may be assessed in the United States by our team in Cambridge. We may keep the information you submitted for up to three years, and use it to keep you informed of other opportunities that might be a good fit for you. If you would like to know more about how we use your personal data please review our Recruiting Privacy Notice here , where you can also find information on how to update your contact preferences. In the meantime, check out our culture code ! Thanks again, The HubSpot Recruiting Team HubSpot is committed to a welcoming and accessible candidate experience. If you need accommodations or assistance to apply to a position or during the recruitment process, please send your request to interviewaccommodations@hubspot.com . This information will be treated as confidential and used only for the purpose of determining an appropriate accommodation for the interview process.

email body: Dear Srisankaet, We’re the largest insurer of cars and homes in the United States and we are excited that you’re exploring a career with us! We know the hiring process can be stressful, especially while you wait for next steps along the way. It is important that you keep an eye on your e-mail, so you don’t miss any attempts to contact you. Your job application has been successfully received for the following position: 2023-33008 2024 Summer Intern Software Engineer - PCM Here are two tips to help you out while you wait. 1. Learn more about State Farm! Check out our YouTube channel to learn more about our "neighborhood", take a virtual tour of our offices, and see what your day might look like. Our careers page includes information on the entire employment process. (e.g. Pre-employment testing, interviews, background process, etc.) 2. If selected for an interview with Human Resources, you will receive an email invitation (you may need to check your spam/junk folder) with a link to record your video interview. • We value your time – the video interview can be completed at your convenience anytime, anywhere. Your digital interview can be shared with hiring managers which can lead to the next step in the process faster! • We value fairness – each candidate is asked the same questions in the same way. Your dashboard will provide access to your candidate profile, your active jobs and any tasks that require action. Sincerely, State Farm This is an automated email response. Please do not reply. email subject: Srisankaet,  Hear from Target and Verizon on how to make your application stand out this job search season
email body: Deadline Approaching Hi Srisankaet, I'm reaching out from RippleMatch as I wanted to invite you to our upcoming career advice event; Navigating Applications: Tips for Standing Out From a Sea of Applicants on Thu, Sep 7 - 3:00 PM to 4:00 PM EDT . As the fall recruitment season kicks off, our team is planning a series of career advice webinars to help our users get the most out of their job search. Did you know that most companies open their applications and recruit heavily in early September into October? To ensure you have your best shot at landing a job or internship, we wanted to help you prepare to have your application stand out. We're hosting this event with recruiters from Target, Verizon, and McMaster-Carr to share some expert advice on navigating applications. Our guests will be sharing their insights about how you can tailor your application to stand out to recruiters, refine your resume, and determine which opportunities are worth applying for. They also will answer questions submitted by attendees during the webinar! Even if you can't attend live, we recommend RSVPing as we'll be sure to share the recording following the event. If you want to learn more about the event happening on Sept 7, 3-4pm ET, just click the link or button below where you'll have the chance to register. If you have any questions, feel free to reach out! Navigating Applications: Tips for Standing Out From a Sea of Applicants Hope you'll be able to tune in! Best, Kate Beckman Director, Brand & Community Register Here Now 5 West 19th Street 6th Floor New York, NY 10011 ❤️ LinkedIn Top 50 Startups - 20th Inc. email subject: Thank you for applying to PIMCO!
email body: Hi Srisankaet, Thank you for applying to our 2024 Summer Intern - Technology Analyst, Software Engineering, US opportunity! Your application has been received and will be reviewed by the hiring team. If you've applied to... • An Analyst role: If you are selected to continue in the interview process, a recruiter will be in contact with you to provide more details and outline next steps. If you are not selected for the next round we will let you know by email. • A Technology-focused role, such as Software Engineering or Data Science: If eligible, you'll receive an invitation to complete a HackerRank assessment when the next round of applications are reviewed. • A Graduate role: o On-Campus Schools: If you have also applied via your career office platform and are completing this application as a supporting step to that process; we will provide updates via your school’s platform according to their timeline. o Off-Campus Schools: If PIMCO does not participate in on-campus recruiting at your institution and this is your sole application platform to our program; we will reach out directly via the email address you have provided to inform you of next steps in the review process. General Applicant Tips: • Application review and interviews are conducted on a rolling basis. • All interviews will consist of both technical and behavioral questions, and additional info will be shared with all interview invitations. Tip: Don't forget that it's a good idea to do your research on the firm and what's important to us. • We encourage you to consider what roles fit your interests and skillsets. Therefore, we do not recommend applying to more than three roles. Summer Internship Program Tips: • If you have any offers with upcoming deadlines, send us an email and we'll see what we can do to accommodate your timeline. • Our Summer internship program runs on a 10-week schedule from mid-June to mid-August. Please note that we're currently unable to offer internship programs outside of this timeframe. Learn more about PIMCO's teams , inclusion and diversity initiatives , and investment processes . Additionally, be sure to check out the PIMCO blog for insights from some of our top economists and visit our Student page and YouTube Channel for more on our programs and interview process. If you have any questions in the meantime, please contact us at Campus.Recruiting@pimco.com Best, PIMCO Campus Recruiting To log in to your candidate home account, please use the below URL: https://pimco.wd1.myworkdayjobs.com/pimco-careers/userHome This email was intended for srisankaetgt@gmail.com

email subject: Allianz - Update - News about your application
email body: Dear Srisankaet Cheemalamarri, We appreciate your consideration of Allianz as your next employer. We also know that preparing application documents takes time, and thank you for your efforts. After carefully reviewing your application for the position AZ Tech Intern, we have chosen not to move forward with your application as other applicants are a closer match to the requirements of the job. We would like to encourage you to consider the following: 1. Check out other job opportunities you might find suitable, and feel free to apply: Allianz Careers . 2. If you have not already made your candidate profile available to all of our recruiters worldwide, please do so. This way, all recruiters are able to search and find your profile in our global recruiting system, and proactively reach out to you. 3. Set up a job alert which will send you suitable jobs based on your search criteria via email. You can set it up in your candidate profile. 4. Provide feedback on your application experience with us on Glassdoor: www.glassdoor.com/Reviews/Allianz-Munich-Reviews-EI_IE3062.htm . We hope you still consider Allianz an attractive employer. Kind regards, Your Allianz Recruiting Team Allianz – Let’s care for tomorrow.
